odbcinst -q -d
You should see [ODBC Driver 18 for SQL Server] or similar. If it's missing, install it:

bash
curl https://packages.microsoft.com/keys/microsoft.asc | sudo apt-key add -
curl https://packages.microsoft.com/config/ubuntu/$(lsb_release -rs)/prod.list | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/mssql-release.list
sudo apt-get update
sudo ACCEPT_EULA=Y apt-get install -y msodbcsql18 unixodbc-dev
2. Test the connection manually from Airflow
bash
sudo -u airflow /opt/airflow/venv/bin/python -c "
import pymssql
conn = pymssql.connect(server='YOUR_MSSQL_HOST', user='YOUR_USER', password='YOUR_PASSWORD', database='webDB')
print('Connection OK')
conn.close()
"
